{
  "texts": [
    "The most extreme kind of non-convergence is referred to as mode collapse.",
    "In contrast to prepare additional models, such an image classifier, for use, D and G training losses or accuracy only measure D and G separately, not the GAN's overall performance or the quality of the visuals obtained.",
    "The GAN model \"works very well indeed\" in case the generator and discriminator reach equilibrium if discriminator loss is 0.5.",
    "To enhance GAN convergence, other regularization approaches are also applied.",
    "This was accomplished by introducing noise to discriminator inputs, as mentioned by Arjovsky et al. [29], and by penalizing discriminator weights, as recommended by Roth et al."
  ]
}